						<summary>

						<p>This registers a gift of 20 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold made by (the chief) <hi rend="bold">Tennavaṉ Maḻanāṭṭuvēḷāṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Koṟṟaṉ Māṟaṉ</hi>, for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple with an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee daily, and 20 cows (for ghee) for performing the sacred bath of the god on the day of <hi rend="italic">saṅkrānti</hi> in each month. The donor seems to be the <hi rend="bold">same as Śembiyaṉ Maḻanāṭṭuvēḷāṉ</hi> mentioned in an inscription attributable to <hi rend="bold">Āditya I</hi> (<hi rend="italic">S.I.I.</hi> Vol. XIII, No. 313). This may be assigned to <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
